<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[498,1542,535,802]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
DISTRIBUTION AND ECOLOGY. Former records from the Azores (
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson CW" box="[1328,1506,536,562]" journalOrPublisher="London: Macmillan and Co" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref11742" refString="Thomson CW. 1873. The depths of the sea. London: Macmillan and Co., 527." title="The depths of the sea" type="book" year="1873">
<emphasis box="[1328,1506,536,562]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Thomson, 1873</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
), and the Canary Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson CW" box="[778,951,576,602]" journalOrPublisher="Challenger" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1876" part="1873" refId="ref11762" refString="Thomson CW. 1877. The voyage of the &quot; Challenger &quot;: the Atlantic, a preliminary account of the general results of the exploring voyage of H. M. S - &quot; Challenger &quot; during the year 1873 and the early part of the year 1876. Vol. 1. London: Macmillan and Co., 424." title="The voyage of the &quot; Challenger &quot;: the Atlantic, a preliminary account of the general results of the exploring voyage of H. M. S" type="journal article" year="1877">
<emphasis box="[778,951,576,602]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Thomson, 1877</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schulze FE" box="[964,1114,576,602]" journalOrPublisher="M. S. ' Challenger ', Zoology" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 514" part="21" refId="ref11260" refString="Schulze FE. 1887. Report on the Hexactinellida collected by H. M. S. ' Challenger' during the years 1873 - 1876. Report on the scienti fi c results of the voyage of H. M. S. ' Challenger ', Zoology 21: 1 - 514." title="Report on the Hexactinellida collected by H. M. S. ' Challenger' during the years 1873 - 1876. Report on the scienti fi c results of the voyage of H" type="journal article" year="1887">
<emphasis box="[964,1114,576,602]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Schulze, 1887</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
), 2,789–4,022 m deep (
<bibRefCitation author="Tabachnick KR &amp; Menshenina LL" editor="Hooper JNA &amp; Van Soest RWM" journalOrPublisher="New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1267 - 1280" refId="ref11689" refString="Tabachnick KR, Menshenina LL. 2002. Family Pheronematidae Gray, 1870. In: Hooper JNA, Van Soest RWM, eds. Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, 1267 - 1280." title="Family Pheronematidae Gray" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2" year="2002">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Tabachnick &amp; Menshenina, 2002</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[860,875,616,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">fi</emphasis>
rst 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[913,928,616,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">fi</emphasis>
nding of the species in the South Atlantic, where it is thus far only known from the São Paulo Ridge (SW Atlantic) (present paper), at 3,060 m depth. The single specimen collected was growing on basaltic rock with other sponges likely of the same species, albeit in very low densities. No epibiontic macro- or megafauna could be seen from the images obtained (
<figureCitation box="[871,935,774,802]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[524,589,1088,1110]" captionTargetBox="[498,1541,234,1075]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[498,1534,234,1060]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2 Poliopogon amadou specimen (MNRJ 17629). (A–C) Specimen in situ, (B and C) holotype; (D) Detail of skeleton meshes (200 mm). Full-size DOI: 10.7717/peerj.9431/fig-2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4624214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4624214/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[498,1542,838,1303]" box="[498,600,838,865]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading bold="true" box="[498,600,838,865]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="0">Remarks</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[498,1542,838,1303]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The single specimen collected by the Iata Piuna expedition matches the original description of 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson CW" box="[669,860,917,944]" journalOrPublisher="Challenger" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1876" part="1873" refId="ref11762" refString="Thomson CW. 1877. The voyage of the &quot; Challenger &quot;: the Atlantic, a preliminary account of the general results of the exploring voyage of H. M. S - &quot; Challenger &quot; during the year 1873 and the early part of the year 1876. Vol. 1. London: Macmillan and Co., 424." title="The voyage of the &quot; Challenger &quot;: the Atlantic, a preliminary account of the general results of the exploring voyage of H. M. S" type="journal article" year="1877">
<emphasis box="[669,860,917,944]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Thomson (1877)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
and redescription by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tabachnick KR &amp; Menshenina LL" box="[1120,1518,917,944]" editor="Hooper JNA &amp; Van Soest RWM" journalOrPublisher="New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1267 - 1280" refId="ref11689" refString="Tabachnick KR, Menshenina LL. 2002. Family Pheronematidae Gray, 1870. In: Hooper JNA, Van Soest RWM, eds. Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, 1267 - 1280." title="Family Pheronematidae Gray" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2" year="2002">
<emphasis box="[1120,1518,917,944]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Tabachnick &amp; Menshenina (2002)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
. The latter authors mentioned that whereas macramphidiscs are clearly separable from the smaller amphidiscs, separation of second and third categories as mesamphidiscs and micramphidiscs is not always straightforward. It is not clear to us whether 
<bibRefCitation author="Tabachnick KR &amp; Menshenina LL" editor="Hooper JNA &amp; Van Soest RWM" journalOrPublisher="New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1267 - 1280" refId="ref11689" refString="Tabachnick KR, Menshenina LL. 2002. Family Pheronematidae Gray, 1870. In: Hooper JNA, Van Soest RWM, eds. Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, 1267 - 1280." title="Family Pheronematidae Gray" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2" year="2002">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Tabachnick &amp; Menshenina (2002)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
were referring to every specimen as a rule, the holotype included.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[498,1542,838,1303]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Regardless, in our material the three categories were clearly separable, if not entirely on the basis of dimensions, but surely when the micromorphology of these microscleres was taken into account. The rare hexadiscs seen in our specimen had previously been reported from a single specimen from the Great Meteor Bank (29 58 
<emphasis box="[1187,1195,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">′</emphasis>
51.560 4 
<emphasis box="[1286,1298,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">″</emphasis>
N/28 29 
<emphasis box="[1396,1404,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">′</emphasis>
12.645 6 
<emphasis box="[1495,1507,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">″</emphasis>
W, 2,480–2,550 m depth; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tabachnick KR &amp; Menshenina LL" box="[761,1147,1276,1303]" editor="Hooper JNA &amp; Van Soest RWM" journalOrPublisher="New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1267 - 1280" refId="ref11689" refString="Tabachnick KR, Menshenina LL. 2002. Family Pheronematidae Gray, 1870. In: Hooper JNA, Van Soest RWM, eds. Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, 1267 - 1280." title="Family Pheronematidae Gray" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2" year="2002">
<emphasis box="[761,1147,1276,1303]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Tabachnick &amp; Menshenina, 2002</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
